Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{some}, season with
@salt{some} and @black pepper{some}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat the @butter{20%grams} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once melted, add the onion, season with salt and pepper and fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}. Add the @sugar{1%tsp} and cook
until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

While the onion fries, trim the @Brussels sprouts{200%grams} and halve through
the root. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the Brussels sprouts on one side #baking tray{}. Drizzle over some oil and
season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the chips have 20 mins remaining, add the sprouts the oven and roast on the
middle shelf until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Once the sprouts have been in the oven for 5 mins, lay the @British streaky
bacon{4%rashers} in a single layer onto a lined baking tray and bake on the
middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and crispy, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

Turn the sprouts halfway through and toss in the @balsamic vinegar{12%milliliters},
then return to the oven for the remaining roasting time.

When the onion has caramelised, add the @sliced mushrooms{180%grams} to the pan.
Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{80%grams}. Halve the
@ciabattas{2}.

Add the garlic to the mushrooms for the last min of cooking time and fry until
fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Spoon the mushroom mixture onto the base of each ciabatta. Top with the grated
cheese and bacon rashers, then sandwich shut with the ciabatta lids and firmly
press all the ingredients inside.

Give the frying pan a quick wipe, then add a drizzle of oil and return to a
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sandwiches, pressing down with a #spatula{} or
#heavy-bottomed pan{}. Cook, pressing occasionally, until the bread is golden
and toasted and the cheese has melted, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Once the sprouts are roasted, drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and toss until
coated.

Once the chips are ready, sprinkle over the @truffle zest{1%sachet} and toss
together.

When everything's ready, share the mushroom grilled cheese sandwiches between
your plates.

Serve the honey-balsamic Brussels sprouts and truffle chips alongside with
@mayo{2%tbsp} for dipping.

Enjoy!